{"descriptions":[{"id":1403,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe marker \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདུ་\u003c/span\u003e (and its variants \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསུ་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརུ་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཏུ་\u003c/span\u003e) has locative (with or without movement) case functions. It also functions as adverbial suffix and marker of object incorporation.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eExamples in the locative\u003c/em\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eགཡོན་དུ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;On / to the left\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eགཡས་སུ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;On / to the right\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརྒྱ་གར་དུ་འགྲོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To go to India\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརྡོ་རྗེ་གླིང་དུ་སྡོད་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To live in Darjeeling\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདུས་སུ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;At the time\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eལག་ཏུ་ཕྲེང་བ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;A rosary in the hand\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཕ་ཡུལ་རྒྱབ་ཏུ་བསྐྱུར་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To leave one\u0026rsquo;s native land behind\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eExamples of object incorporation\u003c/em\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདཔལ་དུ་འབར་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To be resplendent\u0026rdquo; (Literally: \u0026ldquo;To blaze in glory\u0026rdquo;) \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐུང་དུ་གཏོང་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To shorten\u0026rdquo; (Literally: \u0026ldquo;To send to small\u0026rdquo;)\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eExamples of adverbial use\u003c/em\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eལྷག་པར་དུ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Particularly\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eངེས་པར་དུ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Absolutely\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eNote that the marker \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདུ་\u003c/span\u003e (and its variants), as well as the marker \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eལ་\u003c/span\u003e are associated with the adverb \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཇེ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;even more\u0026rdquo; which is used only in the literary language. In the spoken language, the oblique case \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདུ་\u003c/span\u003e (or rather its variant \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརུ་\u003c/span\u003e) alone conveys this meaning.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཇེ་མང་དུ་འཕེལ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To increase even more\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབདག་འཛིན་ཉོན་མོངས་རྣམ་རྟོག་སོགས་ཇེ་ཆུང་ཇེ་ཆུང་ལ་སོང་།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Selfishness, negative emotions, discursive thought, and so on decrease even further.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe marker \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདུ་\u003c/span\u003e has connective functions when it is followed by a verb. It is also used to form purpose clauses.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབོད་སྨན་སློབ་ཏུ་གཏོང་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To send (someone) \u003cstrong\u003eto \u003c/strong\u003elearn Tibetan medicine\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:49 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:49 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}